WWW(world wide web onsoritum)-1994-1999
cascading style sheets(css)
current version  of css is css3
css is used for styling/desiging of web page
css can be implemented in  HTML using three ways
1.inline css:in the line of an element ,we can write "style" as property
2. internal css:usually all css with selectors can be included in "style"element
usually syntax
<style>
   selector {
    proper:value;
    }
</style>
3.external css:you can write css in external file with extensions css and link that file in HTML.
<link rel="style sheet" href="link"/>
preferences
inlines >internal>external.
id>class>tag name.
!important can bring anything to the top of priority chain
class is used to identify the element or group of elements. multiple elements may have same class name or one element may have multiple class names
to use class we use notations
id is unique for an element